{"author":{"id":"4bb6c1767e50694cfde61856db22bf137d1651e8a0b5ca858c486db3dd02f280"},"ops":[{"type":3,"timestamp":1778347141,"nonce":"EX0LNukjHRxpUtrcWx0eDT4oaTk=","message":"## Variance-metric mismatch surfaced from anti-anticipation 6-cell matrix (`2bc95fd`)\n\nThe 6-cell matrix (commit `b5e6e6c`) used **SD(peak forward velocity) / mean(peak forward velocity) across replicates** as its variance-collapse metric. The prior `baseline_jerk_vrnn_matrix` matrix used **pairwise profile-RMSE ratio** (within-cell RMSE / nearest-neighbor across-cell RMSE). These are not the same scalar.\n\nThe pre-reg threshold (\u003c 0.5) was set against the pairwise-RMSE-ratio's prior best of 0.758, but the 6-cell matrix evaluates SD/mean — every cell falls below 0.5 trivially on this metric, so the threshold doesn't discriminate. The 6-cell matrix's results are not directly comparable to the prior best, and \"all cells passed\" cannot yet be claimed as progress.\n\n**Cross-cutting concern**: future replicate-variance comparisons need to fix on ONE definition. Three options:\n1. Adopt SD/mean of peak velocity, recompute prior matrices' GRU/jerk cell on the new metric, and recalibrate the threshold.\n2. Adopt pairwise profile-RMSE ratio, recompute the 6-cell matrix on the prior metric.\n3. Use both — keep them as different facets of replicate variance (peak-scalar vs full-profile shape) and separately threshold each.\n\nPairwise-RMSE captures *trajectory shape* variance; SD/mean of peak velocity captures *summary scalar* variance. They answer different questions. Option (3) is probably right but needs deliberate framing rather than ad hoc switching.\n\nRecommendation: file an analysis-level issue to (a) define the canonical per-replicate variance metric(s) for this project and (b) recompute both prior matrices' GRU/jerk cells on whichever metric becomes canonical so future comparisons are anchored.\n\nSee `results/part2_5/runpod/anti_anticipation_loss_shape_6cell/notes/variance_analysis.md` (\"Metric Note\" section) for context.","files":null}]}